1
00:00:48,339 --> 00:00:52,969
DEAR X

2
00:00:53,720 --> 00:00:55,764
ALL CHARACTERS, PLACES, AND EVENTS
IN THIS WORK ARE FICTITIOUS

3
00:00:55,847 --> 00:00:57,390
CHILD ACTORS WERE FILMED
WITH GUARDIANS PRESENT

4
00:01:04,022 --> 00:01:06,066
Don't think it's a bit much?

5
00:01:08,401 --> 00:01:11,988
How many guys did you bring
just to take me out?

6
00:01:12,572 --> 00:01:13,907
You should be ashamed of yourself.

7
00:01:16,493 --> 00:01:20,038
So, that's all you have to say
for your last words?

8
00:01:23,416 --> 00:01:26,294
First, I'm going to prep two cameras.

9
00:01:27,962 --> 00:01:30,548
You can install them
at the location I mentioned.

10
00:01:30,632 --> 00:01:31,633
Okay. And then?

11
00:01:32,592 --> 00:01:34,135
Then, my phone.

12
00:01:34,552 --> 00:01:37,055
We install spyware on it
as insurance.

13
00:01:37,138 --> 00:01:38,515
You know, a zombie phone.

14
00:01:39,682 --> 00:01:44,479
Then I put an app on your spare phone
so you can remotely control my phone.

15
00:01:46,815 --> 00:01:48,108
Even if my phone is turned off

16
00:01:48,191 --> 00:01:51,236
we can tweak it so that certain
functions stay active like malware.

17
00:01:51,319 --> 00:01:53,196
Audio and video recording
will still work.

18
00:01:53,905 --> 00:01:56,950
Everything will auto-upload
to the cloud every 30 minutes

19
00:01:57,033 --> 00:01:58,076
so it won't be tampered with.

20
00:01:58,159 --> 00:02:00,245
This feels dangerous.

21
00:02:01,079 --> 00:02:03,623
What are you planning that you need
to prepare this thoroughly?

22
00:02:04,040 --> 00:02:05,583
Knowing too much will get you hurt.

23
00:02:08,044 --> 00:02:09,295
This guy.

24
00:02:21,266 --> 00:02:22,475
You think this is funny?

25
00:02:25,270 --> 00:02:27,897
It is funny. You don't think so?

26
00:02:29,065 --> 00:02:30,108
Hey.

27
00:02:30,733 --> 00:02:32,068
Let's be real.

28
00:02:32,902 --> 00:02:34,445
Can you actually kill me?

29
00:02:34,529 --> 00:02:36,698
Do you have the guts
without your boss

30
00:02:36,781 --> 00:02:39,409
Moon Do-hyuk, giving the order?

31
00:02:40,910 --> 00:02:42,704
You're just his errand boy.

32
00:02:43,329 --> 00:02:45,748
You must be desperate
to find a way out of this.

33
00:02:46,332 --> 00:02:49,169
Forget it.
Mr. Moon already signed off on it.

34
00:02:49,669 --> 00:02:51,629
Whether you die here

35
00:02:51,713 --> 00:02:54,090
or vanish without a trace

36
00:02:54,549 --> 00:02:56,718
it won't be a problem,
you piece of shit.

37
00:02:58,094 --> 00:02:59,387
Take him out.

38
00:03:14,777 --> 00:03:15,987
You scared me.

39
00:03:16,070 --> 00:03:18,698
Because she's more likely to live
a normal life

40
00:03:18,781 --> 00:03:20,491
through you, rather than me.

41
00:03:20,575 --> 00:03:22,619
Tell me. What do you want me to do?

42
00:03:22,702 --> 00:03:25,455
- Anything for you.
- If anything happens, call me.

43
00:03:29,125 --> 00:03:30,877
Why not? Why won't you?

44
00:03:30,960 --> 00:03:32,045
You could be in danger--

45
00:03:32,128 --> 00:03:34,130
No. I don't want that.

46
00:03:34,214 --> 00:03:36,424
Why do I have to suffer?

47
00:03:36,507 --> 00:03:37,550
All right.

48
00:03:38,092 --> 00:03:40,220
- I understand.
- So go ahead, Ah-jin.

49
00:03:41,596 --> 00:03:42,764
Use me all you want.

50
00:03:44,224 --> 00:03:45,475
That's what I want.

51
00:04:31,479 --> 00:04:32,480
MESSAGES

52
00:04:35,358 --> 00:04:36,776
KIM JAE-OH

53
00:04:37,485 --> 00:04:38,611
CONFIRM

54
00:04:41,614 --> 00:04:43,283
How many guys did you bring?

55
00:04:45,451 --> 00:04:47,161
You should be ashamed of yourself.

56
00:04:58,589 --> 00:04:59,590
Check his phone.

57
00:05:03,886 --> 00:05:05,722
YOON JUN-SEO

58
00:05:06,639 --> 00:05:08,182
Have you finished the job?

59
00:05:08,474 --> 00:05:09,892
As you can see, yes.

60
00:05:13,271 --> 00:05:16,065
Make sure to clean it up
without a trace.

61
00:05:16,149 --> 00:05:17,567
Do we get rid of this, too?

62
00:05:17,650 --> 00:05:18,901
It's his phone.

63
00:05:18,985 --> 00:05:20,486
You can give it to me.

64
00:05:21,070 --> 00:05:22,947
I need to check it, just in case.

65
00:05:23,781 --> 00:05:27,201
This psycho dragged the CEO's name
into his threats.

66
00:05:27,702 --> 00:05:29,037
I need to see what he was holding.

67
00:05:56,522 --> 00:05:57,774
Welcome home, ma'am.

68
00:06:25,259 --> 00:06:27,303
CALLING

69
00:06:30,139 --> 00:06:32,308
The phone you have dialed
is turned off.

70
00:06:32,392 --> 00:06:35,937
You will be connected to voicemail
after the beep.

71
00:06:36,020 --> 00:06:38,689
You will incur charges
once connected.

72
00:06:40,983 --> 00:06:42,777
Press one to leave a message.

73
00:06:42,860 --> 00:06:46,781
Press two to leave a callback number.

74
00:06:51,869 --> 00:06:53,996
Your time to press a button
has expired.

75
00:06:55,248 --> 00:06:56,916
Press one to leave a message.

76
00:06:56,999 --> 00:07:01,003
Press two to leave a callback number.

77
00:07:07,385 --> 00:07:09,429
Your time to press a button
has expired.

78
00:07:10,680 --> 00:07:12,473
Press one to leave a message.

79
00:07:12,557 --> 00:07:16,519
Press two to leave a callback number.

80
00:07:24,819 --> 00:07:28,573
Please check the instructions
and call again.

81
00:07:28,656 --> 00:07:30,700
Thank you for using our service.

82
00:07:30,783 --> 00:07:32,034
Goodbye.

83
00:07:35,079 --> 00:07:37,665
Take care of Kim Jae-oh
however you want.

84
00:07:38,791 --> 00:07:40,960
Just make sure
I never hear about him again.

85
00:07:41,043 --> 00:07:42,211
I don't want his name

86
00:07:43,379 --> 00:07:46,632
ruining another meal with my wife.

87
00:08:31,552 --> 00:08:36,557
EPISODE 12: THE FINAL X

88
00:08:48,653 --> 00:08:49,820
Where's Kim Jae-oh?

89
00:08:53,741 --> 00:08:55,159
Where is he?

90
00:08:56,410 --> 00:08:57,495
I had no idea

91
00:08:58,788 --> 00:09:00,498
what this job was for.

92
00:09:02,458 --> 00:09:05,419
If I had known,
I never would have helped him.

93
00:09:06,212 --> 00:09:07,338
What was it?

94
00:09:08,464 --> 00:09:09,465
The cameras.

95
00:09:10,341 --> 00:09:12,677
He asked me to install them
at the construction site.

96
00:09:12,760 --> 00:09:15,680
He said the footage would auto-upload

97
00:09:16,264 --> 00:09:18,683
and that I should collect the cameras
once enough time passed

98
00:09:19,725 --> 00:09:20,726
and hand you

99
00:09:21,561 --> 00:09:23,312
the memory card

100
00:09:24,146 --> 00:09:26,816
and my spare phone.

101
00:09:35,449 --> 00:09:37,410
What are you doing? Throw him.

102
00:09:43,332 --> 00:09:45,876
Two of you stay on the lookout.
The rest go down and clean it up.

103
00:09:45,960 --> 00:09:47,253
- Yes, sir.
- Yes, sir.

104
00:10:40,806 --> 00:10:42,099
I don't see anyone.

105
00:10:42,892 --> 00:10:44,268
Even Ms. Gong stepped out.

106
00:10:45,144 --> 00:10:47,271
I asked them to give us some privacy.

107
00:10:48,648 --> 00:10:50,775
Sit. I have something to say.

108
00:10:54,862 --> 00:10:55,863
I wonder

109
00:10:56,697 --> 00:10:58,240
what you want to say to me.

110
00:11:04,205 --> 00:11:06,874
From now on,
don't touch me without permission.

111
00:11:06,957 --> 00:11:09,293
Don't hug me from behind
like earlier.

112
00:11:10,002 --> 00:11:12,129
Don't even let your breath touch me.

113
00:11:13,464 --> 00:11:15,257
Don't do anything.

114
00:11:17,301 --> 00:11:18,928
That's unreasonable.

115
00:11:19,970 --> 00:11:21,847
Aren't we husband and wife?

116
00:11:21,931 --> 00:11:23,432
Because we're husband and wife

117
00:11:24,809 --> 00:11:26,977
I'm telling you
not to treat me like a doll.

118
00:11:30,147 --> 00:11:31,982
If I'm your wife

119
00:11:32,900 --> 00:11:34,694
you should treat me as your equal.

120
00:11:36,445 --> 00:11:37,446
Isn't that right?

121
00:11:42,326 --> 00:11:46,163
I thought pitying you
and adoring you was enough.

122
00:11:47,081 --> 00:11:49,875
Why should I listen to that?

123
00:11:50,126 --> 00:11:52,336
I'm sure you received
the report by now.

124
00:11:54,547 --> 00:11:58,968
I found a way to corner you.

125
00:11:59,719 --> 00:12:00,970
People who got locked up

126
00:12:01,595 --> 00:12:04,932
and disappeared on your orders.

127
00:12:06,934 --> 00:12:08,060
Now, there's one more.

128
00:12:13,190 --> 00:12:15,025
And I have the evidence.

129
00:12:19,363 --> 00:12:20,656
Let's be real.

130
00:12:20,740 --> 00:12:22,408
Can you actually kill me?

131
00:12:22,491 --> 00:12:24,410
Do you have the guts
without your boss

132
00:12:24,493 --> 00:12:27,371
Moon Do-hyuk, giving the order?

133
00:12:28,330 --> 00:12:30,166
You're just his errand boy.

134
00:12:30,249 --> 00:12:32,752
You must be desperate
to find a way out of this.

135
00:12:33,502 --> 00:12:36,297
Forget it.
Mr. Moon already signed off on it.

136
00:12:36,881 --> 00:12:38,507
Whether you die here

137
00:12:38,591 --> 00:12:41,051
or vanish without a trace

138
00:12:41,135 --> 00:12:44,138
it won't be a problem,
you piece of shit.

139
00:12:44,430 --> 00:12:45,723
What are you doing?

140
00:12:45,806 --> 00:12:46,807
Throw him.

141
00:12:51,312 --> 00:12:53,939
You're not the only one

142
00:12:55,399 --> 00:12:57,026
who can corner me or discard me.

143
00:12:58,319 --> 00:13:00,237
With your perfect little life

144
00:13:00,905 --> 00:13:03,199
a single crack will stand out.

145
00:13:04,825 --> 00:13:06,118
Can you handle that?

146
00:13:07,203 --> 00:13:08,913
Mr. Perfectionist?

147
00:13:15,544 --> 00:13:17,671
So, this is what you wanted to say?

148
00:13:18,464 --> 00:13:20,591
You made me sit here just for that?

149
00:13:27,181 --> 00:13:28,849
When you gave the order

150
00:13:30,518 --> 00:13:32,144
I was there.

151
00:13:35,731 --> 00:13:37,149
The evidence is here.

152
00:13:37,483 --> 00:13:38,776
And so is the witness.

153
00:13:41,487 --> 00:13:43,989
I can't tell
if this is a negotiation or a threat.

154
00:13:44,824 --> 00:13:47,034
Does your dear friend know

155
00:13:47,618 --> 00:13:48,869
that his death

156
00:13:50,746 --> 00:13:52,373
is being used like this?

157
00:13:52,456 --> 00:13:54,708
He'd be proud

158
00:13:56,293 --> 00:13:57,837
he was used for my sake.

159
00:14:00,548 --> 00:14:02,091
It wasn't exploitation.

160
00:14:03,050 --> 00:14:04,635
He let himself be used.

161
00:14:07,763 --> 00:14:10,850
Just so I could have something
to shake you with

162
00:14:11,392 --> 00:14:12,560
he risked everything.

163
00:14:13,769 --> 00:14:15,771
You had everything from the beginning

164
00:14:16,230 --> 00:14:18,148
so I wouldn't expect
you to understand.

165
00:14:56,645 --> 00:14:58,397
What the heck did you do?

166
00:15:00,691 --> 00:15:02,693
Say something.

167
00:15:03,444 --> 00:15:04,528
If I tell you

168
00:15:05,446 --> 00:15:07,364
can you handle it?

169
00:15:08,324 --> 00:15:09,325
Tell me.

170
00:15:10,242 --> 00:15:12,786
I wanted to put a leash
around Do-hyuk's neck.

171
00:15:13,621 --> 00:15:15,456
So he couldn't mess with me again.

172
00:15:16,373 --> 00:15:18,125
And Jae-oh helped me do that.

173
00:15:19,001 --> 00:15:22,838
He walked straight in

174
00:15:22,922 --> 00:15:24,423
knowing that he'd die.

175
00:15:26,759 --> 00:15:29,219
That's what he wanted.

176
00:15:29,303 --> 00:15:30,638
What are you trying to say?

177
00:15:30,721 --> 00:15:33,057
You did nothing wrong,
whether Jae-oh is dead or not?

178
00:15:33,140 --> 00:15:34,516
- That--
- What should I have done, then?

179
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:36,936
How long are you
going to live like that?

180
00:15:37,019 --> 00:15:38,771
I'm sick of it, too.

181
00:15:38,854 --> 00:15:39,855
Jun-seo.

182
00:15:40,439 --> 00:15:42,358
Now that Jae-oh ended up like that

183
00:15:43,192 --> 00:15:44,777
I can't stop anymore.

184
00:15:45,694 --> 00:15:47,488
Is this all my fault?

185
00:15:49,281 --> 00:15:51,367
Who has the right to condemn me?

186
00:15:52,451 --> 00:15:54,244
Who can understand

187
00:15:54,620 --> 00:15:57,456
my situation and my position
right now?

188
00:15:58,123 --> 00:15:59,792
Then, answer me this one thing.

189
00:16:01,460 --> 00:16:03,087
You can stop now.

190
00:16:05,673 --> 00:16:08,175
This is the end, right?

191
00:16:14,473 --> 00:16:15,474
Right?

192
00:16:16,183 --> 00:16:17,726
Please say something.

193
00:16:18,769 --> 00:16:21,480
Please tell me that this is the end!

194
00:16:23,232 --> 00:16:24,650
I can't stop.

195
00:16:26,068 --> 00:16:27,319
I won't stop.

196
00:16:29,238 --> 00:16:32,449
If you knew how dangerously
I'm hanging on to this position

197
00:16:34,410 --> 00:16:36,370
you wouldn't tell me to stop.

198
00:16:59,518 --> 00:17:00,644
This is Yoon Jun-seo.

199
00:17:02,271 --> 00:17:04,273
Does the documentary offer
from last time

200
00:17:05,858 --> 00:17:07,109
still stand?

201
00:17:12,531 --> 00:17:14,366
Hold on, sir. How can I help you?

202
00:17:14,450 --> 00:17:16,201
- What's the matter?
- Moon Do-hyuk.

203
00:17:20,289 --> 00:17:21,373
Mr. Yoon Jun-seo?

204
00:17:23,792 --> 00:17:25,919
I didn't think
you'd come find me in person.

205
00:17:26,170 --> 00:17:27,838
You killed Jae-oh.

206
00:17:29,048 --> 00:17:32,134
Everything you ordered is
all recorded here.

207
00:17:34,011 --> 00:17:35,262
I see.

208
00:17:37,890 --> 00:17:39,016
And?

209
00:17:39,099 --> 00:17:41,435
If you're planning
to do anything to Ah-jin

210
00:17:41,518 --> 00:17:44,855
I'll spread this footage
to the media.

211
00:17:51,070 --> 00:17:54,198
A lot of people are telling me
what to do today.

212
00:17:54,615 --> 00:17:55,783
But tell me.

213
00:17:56,075 --> 00:17:59,620
Do you think I'll just sit still
while you post that?

214
00:18:00,245 --> 00:18:03,332
I'm sure you know I can do
far more than you can.

215
00:18:03,874 --> 00:18:06,460
A cheap video
where my name is barely mentioned

216
00:18:07,044 --> 00:18:08,087
won't...

217
00:18:08,170 --> 00:18:09,588
- Do we get rid of this, too?
- What's this?

218
00:18:09,671 --> 00:18:10,672
It's his phone.

219
00:18:10,756 --> 00:18:11,882
You can give it to me.

220
00:18:11,965 --> 00:18:15,761
This psycho dragged the CEO's name
into his threats.

221
00:18:16,178 --> 00:18:18,013
Anyway, once this is handled properly

222
00:18:18,097 --> 00:18:20,015
put in a good word for me
with Mr. Moon.

223
00:18:20,099 --> 00:18:22,976
I still feel uneasy
about that mistake last time.

224
00:18:23,060 --> 00:18:24,561
The fire incident, right?

225
00:18:24,645 --> 00:18:27,648
If we had killed him properly then,
we wouldn't have had to do this.

226
00:18:28,398 --> 00:18:30,818
Perhaps releasing the video
and audio recordings I have

227
00:18:30,901 --> 00:18:32,528
won't deal a fatal blow to you.

228
00:18:32,611 --> 00:18:34,446
But you know what?

229
00:18:35,823 --> 00:18:37,366
It'll leave a stain.

230
00:18:37,866 --> 00:18:39,034
Once those stains pile up

231
00:18:39,118 --> 00:18:41,620
the perfect reputation
you've been keeping so far

232
00:18:42,663 --> 00:18:44,832
will get dirty eventually.

233
00:18:44,915 --> 00:18:48,377
I can always clean up
when things get dirty.

234
00:18:50,671 --> 00:18:52,297
But are you threatening me right now?

235
00:18:52,381 --> 00:18:54,174
I'm here to warn you.

236
00:18:54,424 --> 00:18:58,011
Because I can't just sit by and watch
you or Ah-jin any longer.

237
00:18:58,804 --> 00:18:59,847
Now that I think about it

238
00:18:59,930 --> 00:19:03,600
your friend also tried to warn me,
and we both know how he ended up.

239
00:19:07,855 --> 00:19:09,064
I guess friends

240
00:19:09,982 --> 00:19:11,316
share similar traits.

241
00:19:16,947 --> 00:19:18,198
Leave Ah-jin alone.

242
00:19:20,576 --> 00:19:22,661
I'll be the one to stop her.

243
00:19:23,662 --> 00:19:26,832
You just take a step back
and watch from afar.

244
00:19:28,250 --> 00:19:29,585
Just like you always have.

245
00:19:48,854 --> 00:19:50,397
I've come to make a confession.

246
00:19:54,276 --> 00:19:56,361
Sister, I know
who killed your family.

247
00:19:56,445 --> 00:19:58,030
It's someone you know.

248
00:20:01,742 --> 00:20:03,535
Actress Baek Ah-jin

249
00:20:03,619 --> 00:20:06,663
invited to the Berlin Film Festival
with The Woman with a Suitcase

250
00:20:06,997 --> 00:20:10,876
is making a strong impression
internationally.

251
00:20:11,251 --> 00:20:14,213
Through her recent film
Amen to Nothing

252
00:20:14,296 --> 00:20:17,132
Baek Ah-jin has captivated
critics and audiences

253
00:20:17,216 --> 00:20:19,885
with a bold transformation
and a fully immersive performance.

254
00:20:19,968 --> 00:20:23,889
Many say that she's at the peak
of her acting career.

255
00:20:23,972 --> 00:20:25,682
Tonight at the Bluedragon Awards

256
00:20:25,766 --> 00:20:29,269
she's considered the strongest
candidate for Best Actress.

257
00:20:29,353 --> 00:20:31,813
Will she take home the award

258
00:20:31,897 --> 00:20:36,068
at the Bluedragon Awards tonight?
All eyes are on her.

259
00:20:38,528 --> 00:20:41,573
- Why are you glowing so much today?
- You look stunning.

260
00:20:42,491 --> 00:20:44,868
It's the same face you see every day.
What's the fuss?

261
00:20:44,952 --> 00:20:48,121
And it's pretty every day.
I can never get tired of your beauty.

262
00:20:48,205 --> 00:20:49,206
I agree.

263
00:20:51,625 --> 00:20:53,877
JUN-SEO

264
00:20:59,466 --> 00:21:00,509
JUN-SEO

265
00:22:39,066 --> 00:22:42,152
You can just leave that.
I can throw it out for you.

266
00:22:42,235 --> 00:22:43,236
- I'll--
- No.

267
00:22:43,779 --> 00:22:45,113
It's okay. I'll throw it out.

268
00:22:45,197 --> 00:22:46,365
Oh, sure.

269
00:23:15,727 --> 00:23:16,728
BAEK AH-JIN

270
00:23:16,812 --> 00:23:19,856
If you ever feel like helping me,
call me then.

271
00:23:20,607 --> 00:23:23,568
Otherwise, don't get in my way
for no reason.

272
00:23:57,102 --> 00:23:58,186
It's Baek Ah-jin!

273
00:25:06,963 --> 00:25:10,425
You're aware the award show is airing
on a different channel now, right?

274
00:25:11,426 --> 00:25:15,222
They say the Best Actress Award is
basically guaranteed to go to her.

275
00:25:16,014 --> 00:25:17,265
That actually works out better.

276
00:25:19,226 --> 00:25:21,144
Because her final appearance

277
00:25:22,354 --> 00:25:25,482
will stay in people's memories
as her most beautiful one.

278
00:25:28,860 --> 00:25:31,738
DIM HEART: TWO FACES OF AN ACTRESS

279
00:25:32,531 --> 00:25:35,242
NOTABLE TRAITS:
ANTISOCIAL PERSONALITY DISORDER

280
00:25:35,325 --> 00:25:37,619
FOUND IN ABOUT 4 PERCENT
OF THE POPULATION

281
00:25:41,873 --> 00:25:42,916
Baek Ah-jin.

282
00:25:46,962 --> 00:25:48,755
She falls within the four percent
of the population

283
00:25:48,838 --> 00:25:50,423
with antisocial personality disorder.

284
00:25:53,385 --> 00:25:54,886
She views others as tools

285
00:25:54,970 --> 00:25:57,556
and manipulates or uses them
to achieve her goals.

286
00:25:57,847 --> 00:26:01,393
At the biggest annual event
in Korean cinema

287
00:26:01,851 --> 00:26:07,774
Baek Ah-jin stands
as a top contender for Best Actress

288
00:26:08,108 --> 00:26:11,278
drawing intense attention
from media and fans alike.

289
00:26:18,743 --> 00:26:20,745
She has never
physically committed murder

290
00:26:20,829 --> 00:26:22,664
but she caused
the deaths of two people.

291
00:26:25,917 --> 00:26:29,170
She has deliberately approached
only men who were of use to her.

292
00:26:32,591 --> 00:26:35,468
She still harbors
an unfulfilled plan to kill.

293
00:26:41,975 --> 00:26:44,728
She is Baek Ah-jin, an actress.

294
00:27:23,058 --> 00:27:25,685
Now, let us begin

295
00:27:25,769 --> 00:27:27,854
the 46th Bluedragon Awards.

296
00:27:27,937 --> 00:27:29,689
Let's get started.

297
00:27:38,657 --> 00:27:39,741
Baek Ah-jin is

298
00:27:39,824 --> 00:27:41,743
the strongest candidate
for Best Actress, right?

299
00:27:41,826 --> 00:27:43,912
If she wins, ratings will explode.

300
00:27:44,162 --> 00:27:45,705
Don't tell her anything beforehand.

301
00:27:45,997 --> 00:27:48,041
Make sure no one gets near her.
Got it?

302
00:27:48,124 --> 00:27:49,626
...Song Kyeong-su.

303
00:27:50,794 --> 00:27:51,795
DIM HEART

304
00:27:52,295 --> 00:27:53,296
Baek Ah-jin.

305
00:27:55,173 --> 00:27:57,884
The elegant and kind actress.

306
00:27:59,219 --> 00:28:00,261
Baek Ah-jin?

307
00:28:00,845 --> 00:28:02,597
She was the epitome of perfection.

308
00:28:02,681 --> 00:28:04,307
She was smart, kind, and pretty.

309
00:28:04,933 --> 00:28:06,851
She stood out wherever she was.

310
00:28:07,936 --> 00:28:10,563
Everyone at our school knew her.

311
00:28:11,272 --> 00:28:13,775
Even the teachers adored her.

312
00:28:14,359 --> 00:28:18,905
But those who knew her well
tell a completely different story.

313
00:28:19,864 --> 00:28:21,032
We met those people.

314
00:28:22,784 --> 00:28:25,412
What do I think of Baek Ah-jin?

315
00:28:26,955 --> 00:28:29,082
A devil wearing human skin.

316
00:28:29,332 --> 00:28:30,417
She didn't have a mother.

317
00:28:31,418 --> 00:28:32,919
And her father was a criminal.

318
00:28:33,002 --> 00:28:35,630
She wasn't normal,
at least from what I felt.

319
00:28:36,798 --> 00:28:39,342
It always seemed like her emotions
were rehearsed, as if she was acting.

320
00:28:39,718 --> 00:28:42,053
Her acting has
always been exceptional.

321
00:28:42,137 --> 00:28:44,723
She switched masks
whenever it suited her needs.

322
00:28:44,806 --> 00:28:47,267
That's why I could never tell
what she was thinking.

323
00:28:47,350 --> 00:28:51,062
I think she has
very little empathy for others.

324
00:28:51,146 --> 00:28:53,356
I figured that was the case.

325
00:28:54,524 --> 00:28:56,985
I even recommended
she get psychological counseling.

326
00:28:57,068 --> 00:28:58,278
TRUE LOVE COUNSELING CENTER

327
00:28:58,361 --> 00:29:00,071
Check this out.
It's about Baek Ah-jin.

328
00:29:00,864 --> 00:29:02,240
Is this for real?

329
00:29:02,323 --> 00:29:03,825
Isn't she terrifying?

330
00:29:03,908 --> 00:29:05,535
How can a human being do this?

331
00:29:05,869 --> 00:29:09,247
Now, we'll move on to the highly
anticipated Best Actress Award.

332
00:29:09,622 --> 00:29:14,377
Last year's winner, Jin Seo-gyeong,
will be joining us to present it.

333
00:29:14,461 --> 00:29:16,004
Please give her a round of applause.

334
00:29:17,839 --> 00:29:19,674
Hello, I'm Jin Seo-gyeong.

335
00:29:21,176 --> 00:29:22,302
Let me announce the winner.

336
00:29:23,261 --> 00:29:24,721
The Best Actress Award

337
00:29:25,305 --> 00:29:27,724
at the 46th Bluedragon Awards...

338
00:29:29,768 --> 00:29:30,769
goes to...

339
00:29:36,566 --> 00:29:38,735
Baek Ah-jin for Amen to Nothing.

340
00:29:38,818 --> 00:29:40,111
Congratulations.

341
00:29:49,662 --> 00:29:51,623
Baek Ah-jin,
the winner of the Best Actress Award

342
00:29:51,706 --> 00:29:53,291
portrayed a nun in Amen to Nothing

343
00:29:53,374 --> 00:29:56,002
who investigates the tragedy
that befell her family

344
00:29:56,085 --> 00:29:58,379
and carries out revenge

345
00:29:58,463 --> 00:30:00,089
delivering a deeply moving

346
00:30:00,173 --> 00:30:02,300
and introspective performance
about a character

347
00:30:02,383 --> 00:30:04,177
in anguish over religious doubts.

348
00:30:04,677 --> 00:30:06,387
Congratulations
from the bottom of our hearts.

349
00:30:23,154 --> 00:30:24,322
Thank you.

350
00:30:26,825 --> 00:30:28,409
First of all

351
00:30:29,244 --> 00:30:30,495
my mom

352
00:30:32,121 --> 00:30:33,122
in heaven.

353
00:30:34,833 --> 00:30:35,917
How do I look, Mom?

354
00:30:39,379 --> 00:30:40,380
Are you proud of me?

355
00:30:40,880 --> 00:30:42,423
Her mother died in an accident.

356
00:30:43,758 --> 00:30:46,553
Her father was
the victim of a murder case.

357
00:30:46,636 --> 00:30:49,889
She was also present
at her lover's grandmother's death

358
00:30:49,973 --> 00:30:52,392
and later, her lover took
his own life.

359
00:30:53,393 --> 00:30:55,436
For one person
to experience all of this

360
00:30:55,520 --> 00:30:57,981
the coincidences seem too extreme.

361
00:30:58,356 --> 00:30:59,899
- A documentary about Ah-jin is out.
- What?

362
00:30:59,983 --> 00:31:01,109
That's a scoop.

363
00:31:01,484 --> 00:31:02,819
Start preparing for revisions.

364
00:31:02,902 --> 00:31:05,446
- Check if any articles are out.
- Yes, sir.

365
00:31:07,240 --> 00:31:10,618
While working on Amen to Nothing

366
00:31:11,536 --> 00:31:13,872
I couldn't help but wonder...

367
00:31:15,874 --> 00:31:18,042
"Where is my God?"

368
00:31:20,003 --> 00:31:21,504
Looking back

369
00:31:23,256 --> 00:31:24,257
I realized

370
00:31:25,758 --> 00:31:27,135
He was inside me all along.

371
00:31:29,220 --> 00:31:30,263
I grew up

372
00:31:31,347 --> 00:31:33,141
in an unfortunate environment.

373
00:31:34,851 --> 00:31:39,188
But luck always followed me.

374
00:31:39,439 --> 00:31:40,857
I thought we were incredibly lucky.

375
00:31:41,316 --> 00:31:43,109
I caught myself wondering
if she was an angel

376
00:31:43,192 --> 00:31:44,819
who had come down for my brother.

377
00:31:45,486 --> 00:31:48,156
But I overheard something
at my grandma's funeral.

378
00:31:48,781 --> 00:31:50,033
Was it someone in the film industry?

379
00:31:50,116 --> 00:31:52,076
Apparently, she was smiling
in front of him.

380
00:31:55,747 --> 00:32:01,002
Every step I took to get here

381
00:32:01,794 --> 00:32:03,379
wasn't easy.

382
00:32:04,839 --> 00:32:06,424
But I never stopped.

383
00:32:06,966 --> 00:32:08,509
I kept moving forward

384
00:32:10,178 --> 00:32:11,888
and eventually, I got here.

385
00:32:13,973 --> 00:32:16,684
Her acting has
always been exceptional.

386
00:32:16,768 --> 00:32:19,479
She switched masks
whenever it suited her needs.

387
00:32:21,314 --> 00:32:23,149
To everyone who walked with me

388
00:32:23,983 --> 00:32:26,361
on my journey to today

389
00:32:29,364 --> 00:32:30,949
I offer my sincere gratitude.

390
00:32:31,449 --> 00:32:33,409
She used the people around her

391
00:32:33,493 --> 00:32:35,912
to make me look
like an idiot and a thief.

392
00:32:36,287 --> 00:32:40,458
Could she have used our boss
to try to kill her own father?

393
00:32:40,541 --> 00:32:43,127
We were like family
when she was dating my brother.

394
00:32:43,670 --> 00:32:45,713
I thought she'd at least
show up once at the funeral.

395
00:32:48,174 --> 00:32:49,258
I was stunned.

396
00:32:49,884 --> 00:32:52,845
Soon after, news came out
that she was marrying a chaebol.

397
00:32:57,141 --> 00:32:58,518
I was like, "What?"

398
00:33:03,523 --> 00:33:06,317
These testimonies about Baek Ah-jin

399
00:33:06,401 --> 00:33:08,611
are not easy to verify.

400
00:33:09,862 --> 00:33:12,740
So, we wondered
whether continuing this investigation

401
00:33:12,824 --> 00:33:14,367
was the right thing to do.

402
00:33:14,742 --> 00:33:16,869
Then, we learned something new.

403
00:33:17,704 --> 00:33:18,955
Rumors surrounding

404
00:33:19,414 --> 00:33:23,209
the suspicious death of her father,
Baek Seon-gyu.

405
00:33:24,377 --> 00:33:28,715
Dim Heart began to track down
the truth of that day.

406
00:33:31,134 --> 00:33:34,679
There were three primary suspects
in this case.

407
00:33:36,222 --> 00:33:38,307
Former baseball player, Mr. Choi.

408
00:33:40,643 --> 00:33:42,770
And the person who was
consistently abused by the victim

409
00:33:42,854 --> 00:33:45,815
and thus had the clearest motive,
the victim's daughter

410
00:33:46,149 --> 00:33:47,233
actress Baek Ah-jin

411
00:33:47,316 --> 00:33:49,152
BAEK AH-JIN
ANTISOCIAL PERSONALITY DISORDER

412
00:33:49,235 --> 00:33:50,403
I remember that case.

413
00:33:50,486 --> 00:33:52,530
It was very unusual.

414
00:33:53,031 --> 00:33:56,492
There was only one victim
but multiple potential perpetrators.

415
00:33:56,576 --> 00:33:59,454
Among them, the one
with the clearest motive was

416
00:33:59,954 --> 00:34:01,497
the victim's daughter, Baek Ah-jin.

417
00:34:08,463 --> 00:34:09,505
Lastly

418
00:34:10,590 --> 00:34:12,550
to everyone

419
00:34:13,176 --> 00:34:14,969
who loved my performance

420
00:34:15,511 --> 00:34:18,306
and showed enthusiasm for my work

421
00:34:18,931 --> 00:34:21,059
and to those who supported me
not only as an actress

422
00:34:21,893 --> 00:34:23,102
but as a person.

423
00:34:23,811 --> 00:34:25,438
I give this glory to you.

424
00:34:30,068 --> 00:34:31,694
I sincerely thank you.

425
00:35:22,161 --> 00:35:25,456
The final suspect provided
our team with a decisive tip.

426
00:35:26,165 --> 00:35:28,626
It was Yoon Seok-ha,
the author of Co-Offender Y.

427
00:35:33,840 --> 00:35:35,383
The incident back then

428
00:35:36,509 --> 00:35:38,177
was planned from the beginning.

429
00:35:39,470 --> 00:35:41,848
It's true that Ah-jin
deliberately sought out

430
00:35:41,931 --> 00:35:43,683
someone kind enough to act for her.

431
00:35:44,350 --> 00:35:47,270
It's also true that
she found Choi Jung-ho and used him.

432
00:35:48,396 --> 00:35:51,357
It would have been easy for her
to win someone over

433
00:35:51,858 --> 00:35:53,234
and set a trap.

434
00:35:54,235 --> 00:35:55,486
Back then

435
00:35:56,195 --> 00:35:58,364
she even had a stalker decoy to use.

436
00:35:59,657 --> 00:36:03,369
When the said stalker hit her,
she immediately called Mr. Choi

437
00:36:03,452 --> 00:36:05,538
so he rushed over.

438
00:36:05,997 --> 00:36:07,832
But it wasn't a stalker.

439
00:36:12,962 --> 00:36:15,756
The person Choi struck
with the bat was...

440
00:36:15,840 --> 00:36:18,050
Seeing you alive
wasn't part of my plan.

441
00:36:18,134 --> 00:36:20,553
...the man disguised
to look like her stalker.

442
00:36:22,096 --> 00:36:23,472
It was her father

443
00:36:23,973 --> 00:36:25,433
Baek Seon-gyu.

444
00:36:39,363 --> 00:36:42,825
When I arrived, Choi was already gone

445
00:36:42,909 --> 00:36:45,161
and Baek Seon-gyu
was lying on the floor.

446
00:36:45,536 --> 00:36:46,829
There was blood everywhere

447
00:36:46,913 --> 00:36:48,956
so I assumed he was dead.

448
00:36:52,168 --> 00:36:53,711
Then, I saw Ah-jin.

449
00:36:58,758 --> 00:37:00,760
She was sitting
against the bathroom wall

450
00:37:00,843 --> 00:37:03,512
holding the bat.

451
00:37:15,775 --> 00:37:17,026
She looked at me and said

452
00:37:18,569 --> 00:37:19,654
"It's over."

453
00:37:24,742 --> 00:37:26,160
That's what she said.

454
00:37:27,536 --> 00:37:28,704
"It's all over."

455
00:37:56,190 --> 00:37:59,193
Other people's suffering
meant nothing to her.

456
00:38:00,278 --> 00:38:03,364
She only ever used people
to achieve her own goals

457
00:38:04,699 --> 00:38:05,700
and discarded them.

458
00:38:09,203 --> 00:38:10,371
That's how she built...

459
00:38:13,749 --> 00:38:15,209
her current position.

460
00:39:38,876 --> 00:39:40,252
Do you want to go somewhere?

461
00:39:42,755 --> 00:39:44,256
Anywhere

462
00:39:45,174 --> 00:39:46,258
without people.

463
00:40:12,701 --> 00:40:15,579
I thought you'd change
if I waited long enough.

464
00:40:17,623 --> 00:40:18,707
But you didn't.

465
00:40:20,126 --> 00:40:22,211
I realized that far too late.

466
00:40:23,129 --> 00:40:24,880
That I couldn't save you

467
00:40:25,798 --> 00:40:28,342
and that I was clinging
to something impossible.

468
00:40:30,719 --> 00:40:32,763
That you could never change.

469
00:40:33,973 --> 00:40:34,974
Exactly.

470
00:40:36,517 --> 00:40:38,894
And you realized
that simple thing too late.

471
00:40:40,062 --> 00:40:42,064
So what? Do you regret it now?

472
00:40:47,319 --> 00:40:48,320
No.

473
00:40:51,532 --> 00:40:54,243
Because now,
I'm the only one who can handle you.

474
00:40:58,581 --> 00:41:00,624
Handle me how?

475
00:41:02,710 --> 00:41:04,336
I have nowhere to go anymore.

476
00:41:06,172 --> 00:41:07,631
If you truly have nowhere to go

477
00:41:08,424 --> 00:41:10,426
how about we go to hell together

478
00:41:10,801 --> 00:41:11,802
Ah-jin?

479
00:41:17,141 --> 00:41:18,642
Are you being serious?

480
00:41:23,022 --> 00:41:25,274
I already decided
to stay with you to the end.

481
00:41:26,859 --> 00:41:28,652
If you stop now

482
00:41:28,986 --> 00:41:30,279
I'll stop, too.

483
00:41:32,656 --> 00:41:33,657
What will you do?

484
00:41:49,965 --> 00:41:53,260
I thought there was nothing left
that could tie me down.

485
00:42:01,310 --> 00:42:02,311
But it was you.

486
00:42:05,147 --> 00:42:06,440
My final shackle.

487
00:42:29,630 --> 00:42:31,507
Let's not do anything anymore.

488
00:42:38,847 --> 00:42:40,307
So that no one gets hurt

489
00:42:42,268 --> 00:42:43,769
we'll only look at each other.

490
00:42:52,778 --> 00:42:53,779
I love you...

491
00:42:57,116 --> 00:42:58,284
Ah-jin.

492
00:43:38,824 --> 00:43:42,745
Last night, the car driven
by author Yoon Seok-ha

493
00:43:42,828 --> 00:43:45,998
crashed into a guardrail
and fell off a cliff.

494
00:43:46,582 --> 00:43:50,044
The driver, Yoon Seok-ha,
died at the scene

495
00:43:50,502 --> 00:43:52,546
and actress Baek Ah-jin,
believed to be the passenger

496
00:43:52,630 --> 00:43:53,756
is currently missing.

497
00:43:54,465 --> 00:43:57,134
The police are investigating
the exact cause of the accident.

498
00:43:57,217 --> 00:43:59,053
WRITER YOON SEOK-HA DEAD,
ACTRESS BAEK AH-JIN MISSING

499
00:44:04,433 --> 00:44:05,768
At some point

500
00:44:06,935 --> 00:44:12,232
your presence started feeling
like a blade stuck in my heart.

501
00:44:15,569 --> 00:44:19,156
Even in death, I wouldn't be able
to understand or forgive you.

502
00:44:21,992 --> 00:44:25,704
So, in this life, I wanted to cleanly
sever anything tied to you and leave.

503
00:44:27,790 --> 00:44:30,626
And I wanted to disappear

504
00:44:31,543 --> 00:44:32,795
from your life, too.

505
00:44:34,088 --> 00:44:35,714
That's the best choice.

506
00:44:38,967 --> 00:44:42,221
I gave you
one last brief moment of happiness

507
00:44:43,722 --> 00:44:44,723
so you can live

508
00:44:45,683 --> 00:44:47,643
the rest of your life
with that in mind.

509
00:44:49,770 --> 00:44:52,690
Maybe this is
the first and last long revenge

510
00:44:55,192 --> 00:44:56,902
I'll ever give you, Mom.

511
00:44:58,320 --> 00:45:00,072
No, Jun-seo.

512
00:45:02,324 --> 00:45:03,450
Jun-seo.

513
00:45:03,534 --> 00:45:06,787
I hope you stay healthy.

514
00:45:06,870 --> 00:45:08,122
Jun-seo!

515
00:45:13,168 --> 00:45:14,169
Jun-seo!

516
00:45:55,878 --> 00:45:57,588
You can't find her anywhere?

517
00:46:00,382 --> 00:46:03,218
No signs of life or trace anywhere?

518
00:46:05,262 --> 00:46:06,513
Fine, never mind.

519
00:46:06,889 --> 00:46:08,098
You don't have to go that far.

520
00:46:08,182 --> 00:46:09,433
ACTRESS BAEK AH-JIN STILL MISSING

521
00:46:09,516 --> 00:46:11,018
Just leave the broadcast

522
00:46:11,101 --> 00:46:13,395
and respond
when they ask for cooperation.

523
00:46:15,689 --> 00:46:18,942
We want to share
a follow-up to our previous broadcast

524
00:46:19,026 --> 00:46:21,361
"Two Faces of an Actress."

525
00:46:21,904 --> 00:46:23,947
We recently learned that Yoon Jun-seo

526
00:46:24,031 --> 00:46:25,866
our informant
and the author of Co-Offender Y

527
00:46:26,325 --> 00:46:28,827
passed away not long ago.

528
00:46:29,995 --> 00:46:32,623
